MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Petrona Thin'.

Petrona ExtraLight Italic (Petrona-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Petrona-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Petrona ExtraLight Italic (Petrona-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Petrona ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Petrona Light Regular (Petrona-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Petrona-Light', Everything looks good.

Petrona Light Regular (Petrona-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Petrona Light'.

Petrona Light Italic (Petrona-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Petrona-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Petrona Light Italic (Petrona-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Petrona Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Petrona Regular (Petrona-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Petrona-Regular', Everything looks good.

Pass

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'Petrona-Medium', Everything looks good.

Petrona Medium Regular (Petrona-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Petrona Medium'.

Petrona Medium Italic (Petrona-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Petrona-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. Petrona Medium Italic (Petrona-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Petrona Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Petrona SemiBold Regular (Petrona-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Petrona-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Petrona SemiBold Regular (Petrona-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Petrona SemiBold'.

Petrona SemiBold Italic (Petrona-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Petrona SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Petrona Bold Italic (Petrona-BoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Petrona-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Petrona ExtraBold Regular (Petrona-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Petrona-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Petrona ExtraBold'.

NID 6 is 'Petrona-ExtraBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Petrona' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold Italic' = NID 1 'Petrona ExtraBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

MS NID 6

NID 6 is 'Petrona-BlackItalic', Everything looks good.
